# Database Rules

## MongoDB with KMongo
Use proper MongoDB patterns with KMongo library:

```kotlin
class Repository : KoinComponent {
    private val database: MongoDatabase by inject()
    private val collection = database.getCollection<Model>("collectionName")
    
    fun findById(id: String): Model? {
        return collection.findOne(Model::id eq id)
    }
    
    fun save(model: Model): Boolean {
        return try {
            collection.insertOne(model)
            true
        } catch (e: Exception) {
            false
        }
    }
}
```

## Repository Pattern
- Place repositories in [src/main/kotlin/data/repository/](mdc:src/main/kotlin/data/repository/)
- Use dependency injection (Koin) for database access
- Implement proper error handling
- Use parameterized queries (KMongo handles this)

## Data Models
- Place data models in [src/main/kotlin/data/models/](mdc:src/main/kotlin/data/models/)
- Use `@BsonId` for MongoDB ObjectId
- Include proper field validation
- Use appropriate data types

## Database Operations
- Use proper indexing for performance
- Implement connection pooling
- Handle database errors gracefully
- Use transactions where appropriate
- Implement proper data validation

## Key Files
- [Databases.kt](mdc:src/main/kotlin/Databases.kt) - Database configuration
- Repository implementations in [src/main/kotlin/data/repository/](mdc:src/main/kotlin/data/repository/)
